# Responsiveness rules

Apply these to every component and page without being asked.

## Approach
- Mobile-first: write base styles for mobile, add `md:` and `lg:` overrides
- Never use fixed pixel widths that would overflow on small screens
- Test mentally at 320px (minimum), 375px (iPhone), 768px (tablet), 1280px (desktop)

## Breakpoints (Tailwind defaults)
- `sm`: 640px  — large phones, small tablets
- `md`: 768px  — tablets
- `lg`: 1024px — laptops
- `xl`: 1280px — desktops

## Layout patterns
- Multi-column grids collapse to single column on mobile:
  `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`
- Two-column hero sections stack vertically on mobile:
  `grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2`
- Side-by-side nav links become a hamburger menu below `md:`
- Data tables on mobile: use horizontal scroll wrapper or card layout alternative

## Typography
- Headings scale down on mobile:
  `text-xl md:text-2xl lg:text-3xl`
- Line lengths should not exceed ~75 characters: use `max-w-prose` or `max-w-2xl`
- Never use font sizes below 16px for body text on mobile (browsers zoom at <16px)

## Touch targets
- All clickable elements minimum 44x44px on mobile (WCAG 2.5.5)
- Add padding to small links and buttons on mobile: `p-3 md:p-2`
- Adequate spacing between touch targets — minimum 8px gap

## Images
- Always use `width` and `height` on Next.js `<Image>` to prevent layout shift
- Use `sizes` prop to serve appropriately sized images:
  `sizes="(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 50vw"`
- Never use `<img>` — always use Next.js `<Image>` component

## Navigation
- Desktop: horizontal link bar
- Mobile: hamburger toggle revealing a full-width dropdown or slide-in panel
- Use Headless UI `Disclosure` for accessible mobile nav

## Spacing
- Use responsive padding: `px-4 md:px-6 lg:px-8`
- Section padding: `py-8 md:py-12 lg:py-16`

## What to avoid
- `overflow: hidden` on containers that clip content on small screens
- Absolute positioning without checking mobile behavior
- Horizontal scrollbars on any viewport width
- Text overlapping images on small screens